{{afc comment|1=Page originally made on english wikipedia in draftspace. g13 deleted and archived on everybodywiki. Go to [[:en:Wikipedia:Requests for undeletion]] to request undeletion of original page [[:en:draft:Succor in Travail]][[en:draft:Succor in Travail]] and import the revisions to here for attribution. View on everybodywiki here [[:every:Succor in Travail|Succor in Travail]]. [[User:Immanuelle|Immanuelle]] ([[User talk:Immanuelle|talk]]) 21:01, 16 February 2025 (UTC)}}{{draft}} [[File:Pomozhenie v rodah 19th century icon.jpg|thumb]][[Category:goodbye $1 1]][[Category: Completion tier 2]][[Category: tier 3]][[Category: categories]] <!--Succor in Travail-->Succor in Travail also known as Help in Childbirth is a {{ill|Marian apparition|every|8=en}}[[Category:goodbye $1 1]][[Category: Completion tier 2]][[Category: tier 3]][[Category: categories]] <!--Succor in Travail-->in Easterrn orthodoxy.<ref>{{Cite web |title=Icon of the Most Holy Theotokos the Succor in Travail - L |url=https://www.istok.net/Icon-of-the-Most-Holy-Theotokos-the-Succor-in-Travail-L.html |access-date=2023-11-04 |website=Istok Church Supplies Corp.}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |title=JB-014 "The Icon of The Most Holy Theotokos Succor in Travail" |url=https://charivna-mit.com/jb-014-quot-the-icon-of-the-most-holy-theotokos-succor-in-travail-quot |access-date=2023-11-04 |website=charivna-mit.com}}</ref> {{ill|ru:Поможение родам|every|8=en}}[[Category:goodbye $1 1]][[Category: Completion tier 2]][[Category: tier 3]][[Category: categories]] <!--Succor in Travail-->==Overview=
'''Pomozhenie Rodam Icon of the Mother of God''' (Икона Божией Матери «Поможение родам») — a revered {{ill|icon|ru|икона}} of the {{ill|Mother of God|ru|Богородица}}, honored in the {{ill|Orthodox Church|ru|Православная церковь}} for aiding women in childbirth. The icon is also known as ''Pomoshchnitsa v Rodakh'' ('Helper in Childbirth') or ''Pomogatelnitsa Zhenam Chady Rozhdati'' ('Helper to Women Bearing Children'). Its feast day is {{СС|8|January|||26|December}}.
== Iconography == The icon’s origin is unknown, but two traditional depictions exist: * The Mother of God is shown full-length with her hands raised in prayer, and the Christ Child appears on her chest, similar to the {{ill|Sign Icon of the Theotokos|ru|Знамение Божией Матери}}. * The Mother of God is depicted with uncovered hair and crossed hands on her chest, with the Christ Child below, blessing with an {{ill|Old Believer sign|ru|Именословное перстосложение}}. The entire image is placed on a crescent moon<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://azbyka.ru/days/ikona-pomoshchnica-v-rodah|title=Icon of the Mother of God 'Helper in Childbirth'|access-date=2022-04-18|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220418185415/https://azbyka.ru/days/ikona-pomoshchnica-v-rodah|archive-date=2022-04-18}}</ref>.
The icon’s veneration was especially strong before the revolution, with the feast on December 26 (Old Style) coinciding with the traditional midwives' festival known as {{ill|Babyi Kashi|ru|Бабьи каши}}, celebrated in southern and western Russia and Siberia<ref>{{СДЭС|Бабин день|автор={{ill|Zelenina, Elvira Ivanovna|ru|Зеленина, Эльвира Ивановна}}, {{ill|Sedakova, Irina Alexandrovna|ru|Седакова, Ирина Александровна}}|том=1|страницы=123–125}}</ref>. == See Also == * {{ill|Orthodox Iconography of the Theotokos|ru|Православная иконография Богородицы}} * {{ill|Blessed Womb|ru|Блаженное чрево}} * {{ill|Sign Icon of the Theotokos|ru|Знамение Божией Матери}}
